						<div id="siteNotice"><!-- CentralNotice --></div>
						<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading" lang="en"><span dir="auto">System call</span></h1>
						<div id="bodyContent">
								<div id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>
								<div id="contentSub"></div>
												<div id="jump-to-nav" class="mw-jump">
					Jump to:					<a href="#mw-navigation">navigation</a>, 					<a href="#p-search">search</a>
				</div>
				<div id="mw-content-text" lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><div class="dablink">Not to be confused with <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/System_command" title="System command" class="mw-redirect">system command</a>.</div>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:302px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg/300px-Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg.png" width="300" height="225" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg/450px-Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/68/Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg/600px-Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg.png 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Linux_kernel_interfaces.svg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.23wmf17/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
The System Call Interface (SCI) is a Linux kernel's <a href="Application_programming_interface.html" title="Application programming interface">API</a> to the rest of the operating system.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>In <a href="Computing.html" title="Computing">computing</a>, a <b>system call</b> is how a program requests a service from an <a href="Operating_system.html" title="Operating system">operating system</a>'s <a href="Kernel_(computing).html" title="Kernel (computing)">kernel</a>. This may include hardware related services (e.g. accessing the hard disk), creating and executing new <a href="Process_(computing).html" title="Process (computing)">processes</a>, and communicating with integral kernel services (like scheduling). System calls provide an essential interface between a process and the operating system.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
<div id="toctitle">
